com.hotmail.kalebmarc.jtools

Class Logger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hotmail.kalebmarc.jtools.Logger

  • public class Logger
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is meant to be used to log data to a ConsoleFrame, the console/terminal, a text file, or some/all of these.

    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • addConsoleFrame

        public void addConsoleFrame(ConsoleFrame frame)
        Use this to attach a ConsoleFrame to the current Logger. Attaching a ConsoleFrame will display logs to the attached ConsoleFrame. It can be toggled by calling setLogToConsoleFrame(boolean). It's enabled by default when you first attach a ConsoleFrame.
        Parameters:
        frame - the frame to be attached to the log
        See Also:
        setLogToConsoleFrame(boolean)

      • addLogFile

        public void addLogFile(java.lang.String file)
        Use this to attach a File to the current Logger. Attaching a File will display logs to the attached File. It can be toggled by calling setLogToFile(boolean). It's enabled by default when you first attach a File.
        Parameters:
        file - the path to the file you want to log to (In String format)
        See Also:
        setLogToFile(boolean)
